1. These products contain negligible amounts of iron, calcium, protein, starch, fiber, fat or vitamins. 2. Regular soft drinks (other than Diet Slice, Diet Mandarin Orange Slice, Diet Apple Slice, and Diet Cherry Cola Slice) are sweetened primarily with high fructose corn syrup, but sucrose, medium invert sugar or blends of these sweeteners are also used. In the finished product, these sugars result in a mixture of fructose, glucose and sucrose. 3. Caffeine is not added to Cherry Cola Slice or Diet Cherry Cola Slice. There are trace amounts of caffeine present due to the addition of natural cola flavors. For comparison, decaffeinated coffee contains 0.6 milligrams of caffeine per fluid ounce: Cherry Cola Slice contains 93% less caffeine than the amount found in decaffeinated coffee. 4. Sodium and potassium contributions do not include the contribution from water and sugars used at the bottling plant, which will vary according to the local supply. For comparison, most local water supplies contain less than 3.0 milligrams of sodium per fluid ounce, making soft drinks contribute an average of less than 1% of estimated daily sodium intake. Values for Slice products are calculated using the average contribution from juice. Date: October, 1986 Only the finest ingredients are used in the production of Pepsi-Cola Company beverages. All ingredients are safe and approved for use by the Federal Food and Drug Administration (FDA). To guarantee our consumers consis- tent quality, each ingredient must pass Pepsi-Cola high standards, rigorous quality control tests, and strict bottling procedures. All ingredients are listed on the label in order of decreasing amount. All Slice products contain a 10% blend of one or more fruit juices plus natural flavors to further enhance their taste. These flavors include extracts of the kola nut, vanilla beans and flavor oils derived from natural sources such as oranges, lemons and limes. Slice is one of the most successful soft drink brand introductions of the past 20 years. With 10% fruit juice, Slice is more than just another carbonated soft drink — its introduction created a whole new category of soft drink. The Slice line now includes a four- flavor portfolio which establishes Pepsi- Cola's leadership position in this new soft drink category: the original Lemon- Lime Slice, Mandarin Orange Slice, Cherry Cola Slice and Apple Slice. Diet versions of all Slice flavors are sweetened with 100% NutraSweet. Slice is a natural for consumers who are looking for the added value of real fruit juice in their soft drinks. <::logo: Pepsi PEPSI The text "PEPSI" is centered within a circular design, all enclosed by a rectangular border.::> PEPSI-COLA COMPANY, PURCHASE, NEW YORK 10577 Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/hjpj0226
